The Decline of Traditional Click-Through Rates—and What Replaces Them

One of the most discussed impacts of SGE is the potential decline in organic click-through rates. When Google answers a query directly, fewer users may click on individual search results.

However, for B2B marketers, this is not the end of organic value—it is a shift in how value is created.

Instead of measuring success purely by traffic, marketers must focus on:

Brand visibility within AI-generated responses

Influence on buyer perception and trust

Engagement across multiple touchpoints beyond search

SGE rewards brands that contribute meaningfully to the buyer’s understanding, even if that engagement happens before a website visit.

Content Depth and Authority Are Now Non-Negotiable

SGE favors content that demonstrates expertise, authoritativeness, and trustworthiness (E-A-T). Thin blogs, keyword-stuffed pages, and generic messaging are unlikely to be surfaced.

High-performing B2B content in the SGE era includes:

